# EDF MCP (edf-tickets)

Quickstart writes **`.cursor/mcp.json`** but **cannot** turn the server on in Cursor’s UI.

If ticket MCP tools (`list_tickets`, etc.) do not appear after restart, tell the user to open **Cursor Settings → Features → Model Context Protocol** and **enable the `edf-tickets` server** (toggle on). New or project-defined servers sometimes start disabled per workspace.

If the MCP log shows **Cannot find module** under the **workspace root** `node_modules/tsx`, the fix is **full paths** in `mcp.json` `args` (see latest quickstart); re-run **`npm run quickstart:customer -- --client-root <this-workspace>`** from the framework repo.

**Auth:** `edf-tickets` requires **`EDF_PERSONAL_ACCESS_TOKEN`** (full `edf_pat_…` from the app **Settings → Personal access tokens**) and **`EDF_BASE_URL`** in `mcp.json` `env`. It does **not** use `EDF_SUPABASE_ACCESS_TOKEN`. After changing `vendor/edf-client-kit`, run **`npm run refresh:vendor-kit -- <workspace> --sync-from-framework <framework-repo>`** so MCP code matches the monorepo (published `git pull` alone may be stale).
